[thinking] **Considering Java structure constraints**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm thinking about the Java setup and whether I can use `java.protocol.handler.pkgs` with a nested handler. It seems I shouldn't mix top-level public classes, as Java forbids it. Maybe I could create a package for the handler, but the user wants the active class only. The idea of one-to-one mapping complicates things since I can't create extra test class files. I think I'd prefer to use a factory within the same test, and I need to check the dependencies in `build.gradle`.
[thinking] 
